From f93ccdfbd0ef2c506d94648b11ef5323df616bce Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Hariharan Ramanathan <hramanat@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Fri, 11 Jul 2025 16:35:53 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 1/4] ath12k: UPSTREAM: DP: Add telemetry support for device
 level stats

This patch adds initial support for telemetry in ath12k by enabling
parsing, fetching and filling device level statistics.

Vendor subcommand: QCA_NL80211_VENDOR_SUBCMD_WLAN_TELEMETRY_WIPHY

The handler of this vendor subcommand will queue incoming requests into
a workqueue, ensuring no stats request is lost. The workqueue processes
each request by invoking the appropriate stats fetch call and sends the
response via a vendor event.

The stats can be fetched across multiple hierarchy levels, which will
include:

1. Device stats
2. Radio stats
3. Vif stats
4. Peer stats

Only device level stats are supported in this patch. Support for the
remaining levels will be added in subsequent changes.

Patch-dependency:
0417-UPSTREAM-DP-wifi-ath12k-Support-for-Aggregate-stats.patch

Signed-off-by: Hariharan Ramanathan <hramanat@qti.qualcomm.com>
